[div id:"packaging" style:`{ display: 'none' }`]
  [div className:"content"]Companies are using machine learning to do efficient and sustainable packaging. ML techniques can detect defects in packaging and suggest optimal packaging. The [European Union estimated](https://joint-research-centre.ec.europa.eu/scientific-activities-z/sustainable-product-policy_en#:~:text=It%20is%20estimated%20that%20over%2080%25%20of%20all%20product%2Drelated%20environmental%20impacts%20are%20determined%20during%20the%20design%20phase%20of%20a%20product.%20Eco%2Ddesign%20aims%20at%20reducing%20the%20environmental%20impact%20of%20products%2C%20including%20the%20energy%20consumption%20throughout%20their%20entire%20life%20cycle.) that over 80% of all product-related environmental impacts are determined during the design phase of a product. By using ML, we can optimize package design to use less plastic. [/div]
[/div]
[div id:"tracking" style:`{ display: 'none' }`]
  [div className:"content"]Keeping eye on plastic waste and monitoring it at scale is a daunting task. This is a very good candidate for an ML use case. Initiatives like "[a href:"https://theoceancleanup.com/"]The Ocean Cleanup project[/a]" are using deep learning to identify and quantify plastic litter in oceans and rivers. Locating large plastic dumps on Earth can help us in planning plastic management.[/div]
[/div]
[div id:"separating" style:`{ display: 'none' }`]
  [div className:"content"]This is a very obvious use case of machine learning. To recycle plastics, they first need to be separated from large garbage clusters. Combined with robotics, ML can be of significant help. Deep learning models identify plastic and robotic arms are used to separate them from the rest of the pile. Robots can work longer and faster without tiring, increasing efficiency many folds.
  [/div]
[/div]
[div id:"decomposition" style:`{ display: 'none' }`]
  [div className:"content"]What if plastics can be decomposed? What if they take just a few days to decompose rather than years? Let's be honest, cheap production and the immense usefulness of plastics makes them an indispensable part of our life. Although research is going on to find alternatives, they are still not well adopted. If we can find ways to decompose plastics, it can play a crucial role in saving our planet. AI can help design enzymes to do just that.[/div]
[/div]
